{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778980848560,"sessionID":"ses_1cc7ca85effePOzo50a4rGbIPA","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"apply_patch","callID":"call_fh1c9j6799hAuhiNkGgg3qkH","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"patchText":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Add File: /__w/eval-ont-agent-uberon/eval-ont-agent-uberon/ISSUE_COMMENTS.md\n+Addressed in PR #<NN>.\n+\n+I narrowed the logical definition of `UBERON:0000379 tracheal mucosa` from `part_of respiratory airway` to `part_of trachea`, which should prevent `UBERON:0001826 nasal cavity mucosa` from being inferred beneath it.\n*** Add File: /__w/eval-ont-agent-uberon/eval-ont-agent-uberon/PR_COMMENTS.md\n+This change fixes the incorrect parent-child relationship reported in issue #3617, where `UBERON:0001826 nasal cavity mucosa` was being inferred as a child of `UBERON:0000379 tracheal mucosa`.\n+\n+What I changed:\n+\n+- Updated the text definition of `UBERON:0000379 tracheal mucosa` from `A mucosa that is part of a respiratory airway.` to `A mucosa that is part of the trachea.`\n+- Updated the logical definition from `intersection_of: part_of UBERON:0001005 ! respiratory airway` to `intersection_of: part_of UBERON:0003126 ! trachea`\n+\n+Rationale:\n+\n+- The existing equivalence used the broad grouping class `respiratory airway`, which allowed nasal mucosa to fall under tracheal mucosa by inference.\n+- Narrowing the filler to `trachea` aligns the logical definition with the term name and with the requested fix in the issue comments.\n+- I also checked for an explicit asserted `nasal cavity mucosa -> tracheal mucosa` relationship and did not find one; the problem appears to have been inference-only.\n+\n+Validation performed:\n+\n+- Reviewed the imported issue context and maintainer guidance.\n+- Inspected `UBERON:0000379`, `UBERON:0001826`, `UBERON:0001005`, and `UBERON:0003126` in `src/ontology/uberon-edit.obo` using `obo-grep.pl`.\n+- Confirmed the checked-in diff was limited to the intended two-line change in `src/ontology/uberon-edit.obo`.\n+- Reserialized `src/ontology/uberon-edit.obo` with `robot convert -i src/ontology/uberon-edit.obo -f obo -o src/ontology/uberon-edit.obo`.\n+- Re-checked all mentions of `UBERON:0000379` to confirm there was no explicit bad subclass edge to remove.\n+\n+Completed checklist:\n+\n+- [x] Read issue context\n+- [x] Verified affected terms and parent classes\n+- [x] Applied minimal ontology fix\n+- [x] Checked the term back into `src/ontology/uberon-edit.obo`\n+- [x] Reserialized the ontology file\n+- [x] Reviewed the final diff\n+- [x] Committed only the edited ontology file\n*** End Patch"},"output":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA ISSUE_COMMENTS.md\nA PR_COMMENTS.md","metadata":{"diff":"Index: /__w/eval-ont-agent-uberon/eval-ont-agent-uberon/ISSUE_COMMENTS.md\n===================================================================\n--- /__w/eval-ont-agent-uberon/eval-ont-agent-uberon/ISSUE_COMMENTS.md\n+++ /__w/eval-ont-agent-uberon/eval-ont-agent-uberon/ISSUE_COMMENTS.md\n@@ -0,0 +1,3 @@\n+Addressed in PR #<NN>.\n+\n+I narrowed the logical definition of `UBERON:0000379 tracheal mucosa` from `part_of respiratory airway` to `part_of trachea`, which should prevent `UBERON:0001826 nasal cavity mucosa` from being inferred beneath it.\n\nIndex: /__w/eval-ont-agent-uberon/eval-ont-agent-uberon/PR_COMMENTS.md\n===================================================================\n--- /__w/eval-ont-agent-uberon/eval-ont-agent-uberon/PR_COMMENTS.md\n+++ /__w/eval-ont-agent-uberon/eval-ont-agent-uberon/PR_COMMENTS.md\n@@ -0,0 +1,30 @@\n+This change fixes the incorrect parent-child relationship reported in issue #3617, where `UBERON:0001826 nasal cavity mucosa` was being inferred as a child of `UBERON:0000379 tracheal mucosa`.\n+\n+What I changed:\n+\n+- Updated the text definition of `UBERON:0000379 tracheal mucosa` from `A mucosa that is part of a respiratory airway.` to `A mucosa that is part of the trachea.`\n+- Updated the logical definition from `i